Devops with aws (includes Linux & Shellscripting)
Fee: 12k [existing students of sriman sir: 10k]
duration: 9 months
Timings: 7:00 am ist - 8:00 am ist [Monday - Saturday]
         7:30 am ist - 8:30 am ist [Sunday] (if needed, if we are slipping the time will conduct one hour of evening session as well on Saturday/Sunday = 5:30 pm ist - 6:30 pm ist)
Notes: live classroom notes is written including examples and provided to students on weekly basis
All examples are demonstrated live, no pre-written examples
Recordings: No recordings, no videos, no youtube and if any student found to be recording the session, the admission will be cancelled without any fee refund.

Incase of any personal emergency or medical reason, please send us an message in mail/telegram. the session will be recorded and shared with student directly

pre-requisite:
no prior programming knowledge is needed, just be aware of basics of computers should be enough to join this course.	
experience: min: 3 years - max: 5 years	

Who are eligible for attending this course?
1. Freshers are eligible 
2. Non-IT: mechanical, civil, ece, eee, bcom, bsc, pharamacy: can claim experience and get the job
3. Administrator, DBA, Network, Linux, Testing engineer = the final destination is devops only
4. .NET, java, Python, SDET = are eligible for attending devops

Target: entry-level to expertize (professional)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Course Content:
1. Introduction to devops (10 days)
2. Linux operating system (2 months)
	2.1 File Management 
	2.2 User Management 
	2.3 File Permissions
	2.4 Networking
	2.5 Process Management
	2.6 Utility 
	2.7 Package Management
	2.8 Service
3. Linux Shellscripting (15 days)
	
4. Networking (10/15 days)
	4.1 Network Topologies
	4.2 Network devices
	4.3 Firewall
	4.4 SSH
	4.5 Protocols (OSI Model Layer)
	4.6 IP Addressing (Classfull / Class-less ip address)
	4.7 Subnet mask
	4.8 CIDR Notation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ 
5. Virtualization (10 days)
	1. oracle virtualbox (install/configure)
	2. oracle virtualbox networking modes
		2.1 Nat
		2.2 Nat network
		2.3 bridge
		2.4 internal network
		2.5 host-only network adapter
		
6. Vagrant (Virtualization workflow automation Tool [iac]) (10/15 days)
	6.1 Networking
	6.2 Provider customizations
	6.3 Provisioners
	6.4 Vagrant cloud
	6.5 Boxfiles
	6.6 Multi-machine Vagrant
	
7. Java Language basics | Python | .Net (7 days) 
	1. Programming language (platform-independent programming)
	2. packaging standards (jar/war/ear)
	3. how to run an basic java application
	4. how to deploy an web application on a web server environment (tomcat)
		
8. Database (oracle/mysql/postgres)	(mysql) (5 days)
	1. basics of database management system (RDBMS)
	2. installing mysql server on linux operating system platform
	3. basics of tables/relationships
	4. basic sql queries
	
9. delivering/hosting an static web application using httpd servers (apache2 webserver)	 (7 days)
	1. virtualhost configuration
	2. proxy server
	3. delivering an static web application manually and through automationscripts using shellscript

10. Tools (10 days)
	1. Maven (Build Tool)
	2. Git Repository (Branching strategies)
	3. Agile Methodologies (scrum)
	4. JUnit (basics)
	5. Sonarcube
	6. Jacaco
	7. JFrog Artifactory repository (hosting)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11. Ansible (20/25 days)
	1. What is software configuration management tool, how is it different from shellscripting or python programming
	2. Software configuration management tools architecture
		1. pull-based architecture
		2. push-based architecture
	3. ansible adhoc commands
	4. ansible inventory
	5. learning basics of YAML
	6. Installing and configuring the Ansible cluster
	7. Ansible Playbooks
	8. Ansible Modules
		1. File
		2. System
		3. Database
		4. Service
		5. Package management
	9. Ansible Jinja2 Templates
	10. Ansible Roles (Galaxy)
	11. Ansible Handlers
	12. Control Statements (when, loops)
	13. Ansible Vault
	
12. AWS Cloud platform  (200+ services) [20 days]
